to the editor re appeal for privacy after bush twins are cited for alcohol news article june 1 the appeal for privacy seems reasonable in its own right but this is a president who based a campaign on family values pledging to restore integrity to the white house now when it is clearly harmful to the image of this president to have his family under the public microscope he instructs his representatives to raise the flag of family privacy in an attempt to divert the very attention he invited during the campaign certainly he can not have it both ways neil kurlander stamford conn june 1 2001

